    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "A compiled regular expression used to parse section headers. The default matches [section] to the name \"section\". Whitespace is considered part of the section name, thus [ larch ] will be read as a section of name \" larch \". Override this attribute if that’s unsuitable. For example: >>> import re >>> config = \"\"\" ... [Section 1] ... option = value ... ... [ Section 2 ] ... another = val ... \"\"\" >>> typical = configparser.ConfigParser() >>> typical.read_string(config) >>> typical.sections() ['..."
